:["Some characteristic forenames:  German Armin, Erwin, Heinz, Kurt.","German: variant of   Leister  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Alice Leister was born in 1503, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, Peter Kilham, was 33 and her mother, Susan, was 28. She married Walter Kilham in 1517, in Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died about 1553, in Bury St Edmunds, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1503–about 1553":"1503–umbes 1553","1495–1550":"1495–1550","1503–1553":"1503–1553","1518–Male":"1518–Surnud","1521–Female":"1521–Surnud","1530–1586":"1530–1586","1470–1530":"1470–1530","1475–Female":"1475–Surnud","1550":"1550","1495":"1495","1470":"1470","1503":"1503","1533":"1530","1521":"1521","1586":"1586","1553":"1553","1530":"1530","1475":"1475","about 1553":"umbes 1553","1518":"1518","1517":"1517","Bury St. Edmonds, Suffolk, England